[normal]6.1
[normal]              
[normal]The opportunity to 
[normal]increase the number of women and girls p
[normal]articipating within golf is 
[normal]potentially 
[normal]a 
[normal]significant
[normal] 
[normal]growth 
[normal]area and England Golf believes that this can be achieved by delivering nationally co-ordinated programmes focusing on recreational, social and family aspects, whilst ensuring that there are acces
[normal]sible and affordable exit routes into golf club membership for those participants that wish to sustain their engagement with the sport.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6.2
[normal]              
[normal]England Golf has previously conducted research into the barriers and motivations of market segments playing golf an
[normal]d thi
[normal]s has provided valuable insight
[normal].  
[normal]Whilst across all segments
[normal] 
[normal]the main barriers highlighted were time, cost and perception; within the female segments the 
[normal]emphasis
[normal] was more 
[normal]about
[normal] not knowing what opportunities were available to them and how golf can better communicate and market the sport.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6.3
[normal]              
[normal]The research highlights the importance that England Golf places on understanding the requirements of female segments and the ability to ac
[normal]t upon the findings.
[normal]  In addition to implementing a specific women’s 
[normal]marketing 
[normal]campaign, 
[normal]County Golf Partnerships now focus on delivering 
[normal]group taster and structured sessions for similar abilities
[normal] at
[normal] 
[normal]targeted facilities that are 
[normal]friendly, accessible and af
[normal]fordable
